    "body": "### Steps to reproduce the issue\r\n\r\n```console\r\nspack install boost @develop\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe build aborts because the include file `boost/bind.hpp` is not found. The build works fine with the released versions of Boost.\r\n\r\nAccording to the Boost documentation, one needs to run `./b2 headers` after cloning the git repository. I don't see this command run in Boost's `package.py`.",
